        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-21 15:41:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(22 comments)\n\nmany comments, requires major ver increment",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "ec9e7bc590b1933c54003d26dc98a902eab644e0",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1949,
          "name": "Alex Shatov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ashatov@hotmail.com",
          "username": "alex_sh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-21 17:24:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nperhaps instead of multiple exit() calls on each error, it would make sense to collect and report all the errors into logger.error() and only have a single exit() call if any ?\n\nthese exit() calls will drive k8s nuts :-)",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "7fa0147a8792b1c28c4a628c7042219fa81a07e0",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 511,
          "name": "Jack Lucas",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
          "username": "jackl"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-21 17:35:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThe default behavior of k8s is to restart a container if it exits. We could override this in the Helm chart that we use to deploy dh.\nOn the other hand, these exit()s will happen as a result of a defective chart that doesn't set all of the necessary environment variables, so it's something that should be caught early in testing.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "c1935893448d6b8513ad2576f120b962e25ba584",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1949,
          "name": "Alex Shatov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ashatov@hotmail.com",
          "username": "alex_sh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-02-22 12:48:57.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nputting that logic into config and throwing an exception from config.configure() would be much better than exit()\nthat will\n1. allow seeing the main message \"Deployment-handler exiting due to start-up problem\" that happens before the graceful end of the deployment-handler after trouble with the start-up\n2. allow the unit-testing",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
